## Plan

**Scope (TIGHT, 1 bead = 1 commit):** Core slice ONLY — the `retro.Generator` runner seam + `etude retro generate <scope>` command that invokes a configured EXTERNAL generator script over the covered runs' resolved artifacts, then captures the produced retro through the SHIPPED Phase B `retro.Writer` path. `generate = Generator + the Phase B capture path`, exactly as `bench = Runner + Recorder + Judge + eval.Writer`. Generator is selected via an explicit `--generator <script>` flag (like replay `--runner`/bench `--judge`), with a `git config etude.retroGenerator` fallback. NO config block, NO automated triggers, NO sidecar, NO etude log — those are DEFERRED (see below).

**Approach:** Mirror the proven `replay.Runner` / `eval.Judge` seam shape verbatim. Add a one-method `retro.Generator` interface (`Generate(ctx, GenerateRequest) -> (GenerateResult, error)`) in internal/retro, with two implementations: `ExecGenerator` (external script, same strict-env exec contract as replay.ExecRunner / eval.ExecJudge) and `StubGenerator` (test double, mirrors StubRunner/StubJudge). The `retro generate` command resolves each `--subject-run` via replay.ResolveInputs (reusing the covered run's stage output + inputs, pinned to the resolved commit so it never re-resolves the ref — same as bench), materializes those bytes, builds a GenerateRequest, runs the generator to get the markdown body, then threads that body into the EXISTING retro capture path (artifactstore.AddContent role=retro + assemble workflow:retro manifest + retro.Writer.Write) — refactor the body-to-manifest assembly out of retroCaptureRunner.run into a shared helper so generate reuses it and the writer is NOT reinvented.

**Files:**
- internal/retro/generator.go - NEW. `Generator` interface; `GenerateRequest` {Subjects []SubjectArtifact (each: covered run id + resolved stage output/inputs as fully-materialized RunInput-style bytes + ArtifactSource provenance), Scope, Trigger, Producer}; `GenerateResult` {Body []byte, MediaType string, Producer runmanifest.Producer}; `StubGenerator` (Canned/Err, echoes req.Producer) with compile-time `var _ Generator` assertion. Mirrors internal/replay/runner.go.
- internal/retro/exec_generator.go - NEW. `ExecGenerator{Command []string}` satisfies Generator by invoking the script headlessly with the SAME strict-env contract as replay.ExecRunner / eval.ExecJudge: PATH (exact-key extract), ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR (subjects materialized as <NN>-<runid>-<role> ordered %02d), ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE (script writes the retro markdown body there). Sentinel errors ErrGeneratorNotConfigured / ErrGeneratorFailed / ErrGeneratorOutputMissing / ErrGeneratorOutputNotRegular mirroring exec_runner.go/exec_judge.go. Context-cancel taxonomy + Lstat symlink-safe output read copied from precedents.
- internal/cli/retro.go - MODIFY. Register `newRetroGenerateCommand` on the existing newRetroCommand parent. `generate` resolves the Generator (injected stub for tests; ExecGenerator from --generator / git config etude.retroGenerator otherwise — mirror replayRunner.resolveRunner), resolves+materializes subject artifacts via replay.ResolveInputs, runs the generator, then calls a shared `assembleAndWriteRetro` helper extracted from retroCaptureRunner.run (id allocation, refs map, manifest, retro.Writer.Write). Producer/provenance: the produced retro's stage Producer carries the generator identity and Refs["produced_via"]="generate" (capture records no such key) so a generated retro is distinguishable from a captured one; Refs["generator"] records the script spec.

**Generator exec contract (mirrors replay/bench EXACTLY):** strict env, no parent-env leak. `PATH` (exact-key match), `ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR` (covered runs' resolved artifacts materialized as files), `ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE` (the script MUST write the retro markdown body here). Non-zero exit => ErrGeneratorFailed with trimmed stderr; missing/irregular output file => ErrGeneratorOutputMissing/NotRegular; ctx cancel/timeout takes precedence. Input = covered runs' resolved input artifacts + stage output (the GenerateRequest); output = retro markdown body. (replay passes a single stage's inputs; retro generalizes to N subjects, each contributing its stage output+inputs.)

**CLI surface:** `etude retro generate <scope> --subject-run <id> [--subject-run <id> ...] --generator ./retro.sh [--trigger post-bench] [shared producer flags]`. scope validated against the existing validRetroScopes set. `--subject-run` repeatable, >=1 required unless scope=workflow (same rule as capture). `--generator` required (or git config etude.retroGenerator). Shared producer flags (--harness/--model/--skill-*/--git-sha/--message) + --bead/--decision/--supersedes/--gate/--bench/--eval/--ref reused from capture. Output: `generated <commit>\nref refs/etude/retros/<id>` (parallels capture's two-line output).

